ice composition using reinforcement learning (2013) Service-Oriented Computing, pp. 298-312. , Springer; Wang, H., Wang, X., Zhang, X., Yu, Q., Hu, X., Effective service composition using multi-agent reinforcement learning (2016) Knowl.-Based Syst., 92, pp. 151-168; Wang, H., Wang, X., Hu, X., Zhang, X., Gu, M., A multi-agent reinforcement learning approach to dynamic service composition (2016) Inform. Sci., 363, pp. 96-119; Wang, H., Chen, X., Wu, Q., Yu, Q., Hu, X., Zheng, Z., Bouguettaya, A., Integrating reinforcement learning with multi-agent techniques for adaptive service composition (2017) ACM Trans. Auton. Adapt. Syst., 12 (2), pp. 81-8:42; Lange, S., Riedmiller, M., Deep auto-encoder neural networks in reinforcement learning (2010) Neural Networks (IJCNN), the 2010 International Joint Conference on, pp. 1-8. , IEEE; Mnih, V., Kavukcuoglu, K., Silver, D., Graves, A., Antonoglou, I., Wierstra, D., Riedmiller, M., Playing atari with deep reinforcement learning, arXiv preprint ; Silver, D., Huang, A., Maddison, C.J., Guez, A., Sifre, L., Van Den Driessche, G., Schrittwieser, J., Lanctot, M., Mastering the game of go with deep neural networks and tree search (2016) Nature, 529 (7587), pp. 484-489; Moustafa, A., Ito, T., A deep reinforcement learning approach for large-scale service composition (2018) International Conference on Principles and Practice of Multi-Agent Systems, pp. 296-311. , Springer; Daphney-Stavroula, Z., Ugur, D., Urbashi, M., A pomdp approach for active collision detection via networked sensors (2016) 2016 50th Asilomar Conference on Signals, Systems and Computers, pp. 1697-1701; Kyle Hollins, W., Shlomo, Z., A pomdp formulation of proactive learning (2016) Thirtieth AAAI Conference on Artificial Intelligence, pp. 3202-3208; Lei, Y., Jiantao, Z., Fengqi, W., Yongqiang, G., Bo, Y., Web service composition based on reinforcement learning (2015) Web Services (ICWS), 2015 IEEE International Conference on, pp. 731-734. , IEEE; Wang, H., Wang, X., Yu, Q., Optimal self-healing of service-oriented systems with incomplete information (2013) Big Data (BigData Congress), 2013 IEEE International Congress on, pp. 227-234. , IEEE; Goldberg, D.E., Holland, J.H., Genetic algorithms and machine learning (1988) Mach. Learn., 3 (2), pp. 95-99; LeCun, Y., Bengio, Y., Hinton, G., Deep learning (2015) Nature, 521 (7553), pp. 436-444; Karpathy, A., Johnson, J., L. and Fei-Fei, Visualizing and understanding recurrent networks, CoRR abs/1506.02078; Sutskever, I., Vinyals, O., Le, Q.V., Sequence to sequence learning with neural networks (2014) Advances in Neural Information Processing Systems, pp. 3104-3112; Donahue, J., Anne Hendricks, L., Guadarrama, S., Rohrbach, M., Venugopalan, S., Saenko, K., Darrell, T., Long-term recurrent convolutional networks for visual recognition and description (2015) Proceedings of the IEEE Conference on Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition, pp. 2625-2634; Goller, C., Kuchler, A., Learning task-dependent distributed representations by backpropagation through structure (1996) Neural Networks, 1996., IEEE International Conference on, Vol. 1, pp. 347-352. , IEEE; Hochreiter, S., Schmidhuber, J., Long short-term memory (1997) Neural Comput., 9 (8), pp. 1735-1780; Graves, A., A.-r. Mohamed, Hinton, G., Speech recognition with deep recurrent neural networks (2013) Acoustics, Speech and Signal Processing (Icassp), 2013 Ieee International Conference on, pp. 6645-6649. , IEEE; Yu, K., Jia, L., Chen, Y., Xu, W., Deep learning: yesterday, today, and tomorrow (2013) J. Comput. Res. Dev., 50 (9), pp. 1799-1804; Schmidhuber, J., Deep learning in neural networks: An overview (2015) Neural Netw., 61, pp. 85-117; Sutton, R.S., Barto, A.G., Reinforcement Learning: An Introduction, Adaptive Computation and Machine Learning (1998), MIT Press; Mnih, V., Kavukcuoglu, K., Silver, D., Rusu, A.A., Veness, J., Bellemare, M.G., Graves, A., Ostrovski, G., Human-level control through deep reinforcement learning (2015) Nature, 518 (7540), pp. 529-533; Lillicrap, T.P., Hunt, J.J., Pritzel, A., Heess, N., Erez, T., Tassa, Y., Silver, D., Wierstra, D., Continuous control with deep reinforcement learning, CoRR abs/1509.02971; Duan, Y., Chen, X., Houthooft, R., Schulman, J., Abbeel, P., Benchmarking deep reinforcement learning for continuous control (2016) Proceedings of the 33rd International Conference on Machine Learning (ICML); Oh, J., Guo, X., Lee, H., Lewis, R.L., Singh, S., Action-conditional video prediction using deep networks in atari games (2015) Advances in Neural Information Processing Systems, pp. 2863-2871; Caicedo, J.C., Lazebnik, S., Active object localization with deep reinforcement learning (2015) Proceedings of the IEEE International Conference on Computer Vision, pp. 2488-2496; Ohta, M., Kumada, Y., Noda, I., Using suitable action selection rule in reinforcement learning (2003) Systems, Man and Cybernetics, 2003. IEEE International Conference on, Vol. 5, pp. 4358-4363. , IEEE; Strehl, A.L., Littman, M.L., An empirical evaluation of interval estimation for markov decision processes (2004) Tools with Artificial Intelligence, 2004. ICTAI 2004. 16th IEEE International Conference on, pp. 128-135. , IEEE; Bernstein, D.S., Hansen, E.A., Zilberstein, S., Bounded policy iteration for decentralized pomdps (2005) Proceedings of the Nineteenth International Joint Conference on Artificial Intelligence (IJCAI), pp. 52-57; Wang, H., Wu, Q., Chen, X., Yu, Q., Zheng, Z., Bouguettaya, A., Adaptive and dynamic service composition via multi-agent reinforcement learning (2014) Proceedings of the IEEE International Conference on Web Services (ICWS), pp. 447-454. , IEEE; Oreizy, P., Gorlick, M.M., Taylor, R.N., Heimbigner, D., Johnson, G., Medvidovic, N., Quilici, A., Wolf, A.L., An architecture-based approach to self-adaptive software (1999) IEEE Intell. Syst., 14 (3), pp. 54-62; Wang, Z., Schaul, T., Hessel, M., H. van Hasselt, M. Lanctot, N. de Freitas, Dueling network architectures for de