g to the induction of effective and adaptive pedagogical strategies (2011) User Model. User-Adapted Interact., 21 (1-2), pp. 137-180; Cho, K., Learning phrase representations using RNN encoder-decoder for statistical machine translation (2014) Proc. Conf. Empirical Methods Natural Lang. Process. (EMNLP), pp. 1724-1734. , Doha, Qatar; Sutskever, I., Vinyals, O., Le, Q.V., Sequence to sequence learning with neural networks (2014) Proc. Adv. Neural Inf. Process. Syst, pp. 3104-3112. , Montreal, Canada; Hochreiter, S., Schmidhuber, J., Long short-term memory (1997) Neural Comput., 9 (8), pp. 1735-1780; Li, J., Galley, M., Brockett, C., Gao, J., Dolan, B., (2015) A Diversity-promoting Objective Function for Neural Conversation Models, , https://arxiv.org/abs/1510.03055; Narayan, S., Gardent, C., Hybrid simplification using deep semantics and machine translation (2014) Proc. 52nd Annu. Meeting Assoc. Comput. Linguistics (ACL), pp. 435-445. , Maryland, MD, USA; Papineni, K., Roukos, S., Ward, T., Zhu, W.-J., IBM research report BLEU: A method for automatic evaluation of machine translation (2002) Proc. 40th Annu. Meeting Assoc. Comput. Linguistics, Pennsylvania, PA, USA, 30 (2), pp. 311-318; Vinyals, O., Le, Q., (2015) A Neural Conversational Model, , https://arxiv.org/abs/1506.05869; Liu, C.-W., Lowe, R., Serban, I.V., Noseworthy, M., Charlin, L., Pineau, J., How not to evaluate your dialogue system: An empirical study of unsupervised evaluation metrics for dialogue response generation (2016) Proc. Conf. Empirical Methods Natural Lang. Process., Texas, TX, USA, pp. 2122-2132; Galley, M., 4BLEU: A discriminative metric for generation tasks with intrinsically diverse targets (2015) Proc. 53rd Annu. Meeting Assoc. Comput. Linguistics 7th Int. Joint Conf. Natural Lang. Process, pp. 445-450. , Beijing, China},
